events.name: Preview - Caltex Fuel Your School Tech Jam 2018
events.description:
Caltex Fuel Your School - Tech Jam 2016 explores how you an covnert e-waste and old toys into quirky robots. Join us in this exclusive preview to find out how you can bulld a photo booth, make a tiny robot and find out more about the upcoming Tech Jam on 14th and 15th July
Visitors can donate their e-waste for students to take apart during the programme. Items that can be taken apart include - battery operated toys, alarm clocks, speakers etc
Due to safety reasons, large e-waste items such as household appliances or any item running off a power socket-will not be accepted.
events.location: Jurong Regional Library, Programme Zone, Singapore 609732

events.name: TraXion - Building Businesses using Hyperledger Fabric Technology
events.description: Hey Likers, Using the latest Hyperledger Fabric technology, TraXion provides seamless integration and connectivity among networks, businesses and people. Please rsvp on their eventbrite page:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/traxion-ico-tickets-46348788474?aff=eand TraXion focuses on building infrastructure for everyday users. A blockchain- driven environment changes how people do business by enforcing data integrity, accountability, transparency, and trust. Our solution is a blockchain platform ready for business which means it's scalable, immutable, permissioned, and has all the necessities to execute smart contracts, business provenance and data visibility Speaker - Ann Cuisia, CEO of Traxion.About Ann Cuisia: "With her 20+ years of information technology experience, she has led several women startup founders. Prior to entrepreneurship, she has advanced in the corporate scene of banking and finance and have spent a good number of years in payments and donations. She has been a pioneer in the Philippines for helping non-profit organizations achieve its digital transformation and online giving facilities. She is passionate about social impact and is now leading the whole TraXion direction on blockchain for the common good." Event Agenda6.00pm - 10.00pm TraXion Hyperledger Fabric technology

events.name: Social Coding
events.description: A space for women coders to learn from each other, to practice and discuss learnings with fellow peers. This would be a monthly event of informal space to do coding on open source projects. So bring your pet projects along or join one of our existing teams/ projects to work on. Featured Projects:https://trello.com/b/kl2BTwil/wwc-sg-social-coding-projects First timers, please read:Newbies Step-by-step Guide (https://www.meetup.com/Women-Who-Code-Singapore/pages/22271496/Social_Coding_Guide/) Please bring your own laptop. Agenda:6:30p - Start coding! ^_^8:30p - End session Psst, this event is intended for ladies only. All attendees kindly read and abide by the Women Who Code Code of Conduct - https://github.com/WomenWhoCode/guidelines-resources/blob/master/code_of_conduct.md
